ottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Berry","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish and Manx: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Béara</b> ‘descendant of <i>Béara</i>’, a personal name of unexplained etymology; or, in some cases, perhaps an Anglicized form of Irish and Manx <b>Ó Beargha</b>. Compare   Barry   1.","Scottish and northern Irish: variant of   Barrie  .","English: habitational name from any of several places called in Devon named with Old English <i>byrig</i>, dative case of <i>burh</i> ‘fortified manor house, stronghold’, such as Berry Pomeroy and Berrynarbor."],"variants":[{"name":"Berrey","meanings":["English: variant of   Berry  ."]},{"name":"Barry","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Donal, Aidan, Ciaran, Eoin, John Patrick, Kaitlin, Kieran, Murphy, Aileen, Brigid, Caitlin.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Beargha</b> ‘descendant of <i>Beargh</i>’, a byname meaning ‘plunderer’.","Irish and Manx: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Báire</b> ‘descendant of <i>Báire</i>’, a short form of either of two Gaelic personal names, <i>Bairrfhionn</i> or <i>Fionnbharr</i>, both meaning ‘fair-topped’. This may also be the source of the Manx name <i>Barry</i>, whose family's main seat was Ballavarry in Kirk Andreas."]},{"name":"Bery","meanings":["English: variant of   Berry  .","Hungarian (<b>Béry</b>): habitational name for someone from any of various places called Bér, in Baranya, Komárom, Nógrád, Pest, Vas, or Zala counties."]},{"name":"Beery","meanings":["Irish: Anglicized form of <b>Ó Béara</b>. See   Berry   and   O'Berry  .","Americanized form of Swiss German   Bieri  ."]},{"name":"Berrie","meanings":["Scottish:","(Glasgow): from Middle English or Older Scots <i>(atte) beri</i> ‘(at the) manor house’, see   Berry  .","variant   Barrie  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":55,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":64,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":99,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"William De Berry was born about 1160, in Berrynarbor, Devon, England as the son of William De Berry and Unknown. He had at least 1 son with Unknown."},"et":{"about 1160–":"umbes 1160–Surnud","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1188–Male":"1188–Surnud","1132–Male":"1132–Surnud","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","about 1160":"umbes 1160","1224":"1224","1188":"1188","1132":"1132","about 1188":"umbes 1188","1160":"1160","Berrynarbor, Devon, England":"Berrynarbor, Devon, England"},"fi":{"about 1160–":"noin 1160–Kuollut","1160–Male":"1160–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1188–Male":"1188–Kuollut","1132–Male":"1132–Kuollut","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","about 1160":"noin 1160","1224":"1224","1188":"1188","1132":"1132","about 1188":"noin 1188","1160":"1160","Berrynarbor, Devon, England":"Berrynarbor, Devon, England"},"fr":{"about 1160–":"environ 1160–Décédé","1160–Male":"1160–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1188–Male":"1188–Décédé","1132–Male":"1132–Décédé","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","about 1160":"environ 1160","1224":"1224","1188":"1188","1132":"1132","about 1188":"environ 1188","1160":"1160","Berrynarbor, Devon, England":"Berrynarbor, Devon, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"William De Berry est né environ 1160, à Berrynarbor, Devon, Angleterre, fils de William De Berry et Unknown. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Unknown."},"de":{"about 1160–":"um 1160–Verstorben","1160–Male":"1160–Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1188–Male":"1188–Verstorben","1132–Male":"1132–Verstorben","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","about 1160":"um 1160","1224":"1224","1188":"1188","1132":"1132","about 1188":"um 1188","1160":"1160","Berrynarbor, Devon, England":"Berrynarbor, Devon, England","lifeSummary":"William De Berry wurde um 1160 in Berrynarbor, Devon, England, als Sohn von William De Berry und Unknown geboren. Er hatte mit Unknown mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"about 1160–":"about 1160–Desede","1160–Male":"1160–Desede","–Female":"Desede","1